PHASE 7 BEHAVIOR VERIFIED
- Retrieval squads unlock at civilization Lv.0 and deploy from established major or simple bases.
- The squad has 55 HP, 1.2 enemy DPS, no hostile-base damage and intentionally low combat survivability.
- Deployment reserves exactly one available recovery item and prevents direct-player or second-squad duplication.
- The squad follows the road graph, collects for eight simulated seconds and receives no artifact at pickup time.
- Artifact inventory increases only after the carrying squad physically returns to an established base.
- Destruction before pickup releases the item at its original point.
- Destruction while carrying drops the item at the squad's exact road position and keeps a routable road-node reference.
- Withdrawal before pickup releases the reservation without awarding the item.
- Orphaned reservations recover automatically if their assigned squad is absent.
- Recovery missions survive save/restore and complete across active, peripheral and dormant regional intervals.
- Direct player collection remains available and faster when the player can reach the site.
- Retrieval squads enter the existing recovery/reorganization system after a successful return.

ISSUES FOUND AND CORRECTED
1. Direct player collection could remain active while the deployment preview still presented the same item. Recovery deployment now rejects that target before any cost or garrison mutation.
2. Recovery dispatch previously consumed resources and mutated/replaced a ready squad before the item reservation was final. Confirmation now reserves first, rolls back a reservation if payment fails and mutates squad state only after both checks succeed.
3. Existing squad-count and mixed-combat tests assumed five squads and that every squad targeted hostile bases. Tests now distinguish the sixth recovery-only mission type.
4. Current README descriptions of simple-base deployment and recovery were updated to include retrieval squads while retaining major-only restrictions for siege, heavy and expedition squads.

